---
One-click setup (MCP registration + Skills installation)

Usage: cdt setup [OPTIONS] [COMMAND]

Commands:
  mcp          Register MCP server with Claude Code
  skills       Install example Skills
  completions  Install shell completions
  help         Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
      --format <FORMAT>
          Output format
          
          [default: table]
          [possible values: json, jsonl, table]

      --project <PROJECT>
          Scope to a project (name or encoded ID; use --project=<id> for encoded IDs)

      --json[=<JSON>]
          Select JSON fields (comma-separated), implies --format json. Without value: list available
          fields. Usage: --json=field1,field2

      --no-truncate
          Do not truncate fields in table mode

  -s, --scope <SCOPE>
          Scope: local (private), project (shared .mcp.json), user (global)

          Possible values:
          - local:   Private (~/.claude/settings.local.json), not version controlled
          - project: Shared (.mcp.json / .claude/skills/), can be committed
          - user:    Global (~/.claude/settings.json / ~/.claude/skills/), all projects
          
          [default: local]

      --dry-run
          Dry run: print actions without executing

      --force
          Force overwrite existing files (Skills)

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')
